The paper deals with classification algorithms and their application to hierarchical organization of objects. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of hierarchical structures for classification is common in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses experimental results, which suggests that it may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
